description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an opportunity for a self-motivated individual with excellent communication and interpersonal skills to join our pharmacy team at Tameside &amp; Glossop Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post would be ideal for a recently qualified Pharmacy Technician&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will include dispensing In-Patient prescriptions, Out-Patient prescriptions, TTOs and Clozapine and ward based Technician duties including Medicines Reconciliation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the opportunity to train as an accredited checking pharmacy technician when appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will possess a BTEC National Certificate in Pharmacy Services and NVQ Level 3 in Pharmacy Services (or the recognised equivalent Certificated Pharmacy Technician qualification). Applicants will be required to be registered with the General Pharmaceutical Council.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Stacey Walton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Principle Technician Education and Training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0161 922 6290&lt;/p&gt;
